The paper deals with robot motion planning, which is a core topic in robotics, and specifically addresses the challenge of dealing with uncertainty in the dynamics of the robot. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a hierarchical POMDP planner that leverages task knowledge to reduce uncertainty, which suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed planner for navigation and localization tasks, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories.
